ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: What this course is depends very much on who your PI is. If you have a good relationship with them and are going to be doing substantial research during the semester, you might as well take the intensive research course. The only difference from the regular one is the 20-hour requirement, but a lot of people spend that long in the lab in the regular course, too.
Do it your senior year if you have the room for it in your schedule. It gives you a taste of what grad school will be like!
